I"q	<h2 id="version">Version</h2>

<p>Check the version of the Waveshare module and use the example code for <a href="https://github.com/waveshare/e-Paper/tree/master/Arduino/epd1in54">version 1</a> and <a href="https://github.com/waveshare/e-Paper/tree/master/Arduino/epd1in54_V2">version 2</a> accordingly.</p>

<h2 id="spi">SPI</h2>

<p>The 4 non-SPI pins are defined in <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">epdif.h</code> file:</p>

<div class="language-c highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="cp">#define RST_PIN         8
#define DC_PIN          9
#define CS_PIN          10
#define BUSY_PIN        7
</span></code></pre></div></div>

<p>The SPI pins for Arduino M0 / SAMD21G are defined as following:</p>

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>SAMD21G Pin</th>
      <th>I/O Pin</th>
      <th>SERCOM-ALT</th>
      <th>Name</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">19</code></td>
      <td><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">PB10</code></td>
      <td><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">SERCOM4/PAD[2]</code></td>
      <td>MOSI</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">20</code></td>
      <td><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">PB11</code></td>
      <td><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">SERCOM4/PAD[3]</code></td>
      <td>SCK</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

